Citation.sTitle: Viscosity B Coefficients and Partial Molar Volumes of Tetrabutylammonium Bromide in a-Butyrolactone + Water at Different Temperatures
Citation.sAbstract: Densities and viscosities of solutions of tetrabutylammonium bromide have been measured in a-butyrolactone  + water mixtures at various temperatures, (298.15, 303.15, 308.15, 313.15, and 318.15) K. The viscosity  data have been analyzed using the Jones-Dole equation. The density data have been utilized to calculate  apparent molar volumes, V , and partial molar volumes at infinite dilution, V   0. The behavior of these  parameters has been used to investigate the solute solute and solute solvent interactions.
